What is Object-Oriented Programming (OOP) ?
- A programming paradigm that uses the concept of classes and objects.
- it is used to structure application's code into simple reusable piece of codes
that is called classes

OOP Building Blocks
- Class & Object
- Property and Function

Four Main Principles of Object-Oriented Programming (OOP)
- Encapsulation
- Inheritance
- Abstraction (Exposing necessary details)
- Polymorphism
